body:
I'm compiling with -g2012 from master.

A quick trace led me to this, pform.cc:2694

```
if (is_compilation_unit(lexical_scope)) {
    VLerror(li, "sorry: variable declarations in the $root scope are not yet supported.");
    return;
}
```

I'm guessing this isn't an issue easily tackled by a new iverilog dev? I wouldn't mind taking a look at an approach to this feature but I want to be realistic with my time/expectations for now. My skill set is definitely closer to "easy" than "moderate" right now.

Is this already within the scope of an active developer on the project? Where does this feature fit in the roadmap of priorities? I checked the wikia and didn't see anything listed pertaining to this feature. The man page lists 2005 as the default standard, so I'm guessing 2012 is still in active dev?

I can provide a source file if you'd like. 

Thanks for all the hard work you put into this project.

